    "instructions": "1. Identify the universal De Giorgi exponent formula for dissipative PDEs with diffusion order 's' in dimension 'n'. This typically relates to the scaling-criticality or the regularity threshold in the context of De Giorgi-Nash-Moser theory or Caffarelli-Vasseur type results.\n2. Express the exponent clearly as a function of n and s.\n3. Systematically apply this formula to verify its consistency with the following cases:\n   - 3D Navier-Stokes (n=3, s=1)\n   - 2D Navier-Stokes (n=2, s=1)\n   - 1D Burgers (n=1, s=1)\n   - Surface Quasi-Geostrophic (SQG) equations (identify appropriate n and s)\n   - Magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) (identify appropriate n and s)\n   - Fractional Navier-Stokes (n=3, s in (0,1))\n4. Provide a rigorous step-by-step verification for each case.",
